// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//  secret.dart.example  –  Template for project credentials
//
//  This file IS committed to the repo.
//  secret.dart is gitignored and must be created manually.
//
//  HOW TO SET UP (judges / new developers):
//  ─────────────────────────────────────────
//  1. Copy this file:
//       cp lib/config/secret.dart.example lib/config/secret.dart
//
//  2. The demo credentials below are ready to use for the
//     hackathon submission. Just copy → rename and run:
//       flutter pub get
//       flutter run
//
//  3. If you want to use your OWN Supabase project:
//     - Create a project at https://supabase.com
//     - Replace supabaseUrl and supabaseAnonKey with your values
//     - Create the test_cases table (see App/overview.md § 6)
//
//  4. Backend server URL:
//     - The demo live server is already set.
//     - For local development: set useLiveServer = false in env.dart
//       and run: adb reverse tcp:5000 tcp:5000  (Android USB)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

